rm\r\nOperating system and version: Ubuntu Linux 20.04\r\nOBS Studio version: 26.0.2 ppa:obsproject/obs-studio\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\nCan resize Windowed Projectors.\r\n\r\n## Current Behavior\r\nCan maximize window which increases resolution/detail successfully.\r\n**Cannot resize** the Windowed Projector window to any other size. It is stuck at about 270p resolution.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n0. Start desktop environment as `startplasma-x11` (kubuntu-desktop package)\r\n1. In OBS, right click the current Scene's name\r\n2. Select Windowed Projector (Scene)\r\n\r\n## Additional information\r\n- Resize still works fine for all other windows created by the application, OBS Studio.\r\n- Issue does not occur if OBS is run under X forwarding, nor is it encountered if run under Gnome.\r\n- Workaround A: `wmctrl -r 'windowed projector' -e 0,100,100,1280,720`\r\n- Workaround B - all steps seem to be necessary:\r\n1. Disable compositor, log out and back in\r\n2. Open the projector window\r\n3. Attempt to make the projector window larger or smaller using the mouse\r\n4. Maximize the projector window\r\n5. Unmaximize the projector window\r\n6. Attempt to make the projector window larger or smaller using the mouse. This time, hold the mouse down for several seconds.","closed_by":{"login":"kkartaltepe","id":526419,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUyNjQxOQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/526419?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/kkartaltepe","html_url":"https://github.com/kkartaltepe","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kkartaltepe/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kkartaltepe/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kkartaltepe/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kkartaltepe/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kkartaltepe/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kkartaltepe/orgs","repos